tball/brazil-protests-fifa-tax/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldcrunch.com/opinion-analysis/what-the-world-cup-will-do-to-brazil-039-s-economy/economy-corruption-tourism-football-investment-spending-money-debt/c7s14631/#.U5NgAuKZNyM |title=What The World Cup Will Do To Brazil's Economy |publisher=Worldcrunch.com |date=7 January 2014 |accessdate=7 June 2014 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303173208/http://www.worldcrunch.com/opinion-analysis/what-the-world-cup-will-do-to-brazil-039-s-economy/economy-corruption-tourism-football-investment-spending-money-debt/c7s14631/#.U5NgAuKZNyM |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thinkprogress.org/economy/2012/03/20/447727/cincinnati-stadiums-sell-hospital/ |title=After Using Over $500 Million In Taxpayer Money To Build Sports Stadiums, Cincinnati Forced To Sell Off Local Hospital |access-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714001933/http://thinkprogress.org/economy/2012/03/20/447727/cincinnati-stadiums-sell-hospital/ |archive-date=2016-07-14 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Reuters |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-06-05/news/50359174_1_gil-castello-branco-contas-abertas-sinaenco |title=World Cup 2014 leaves Brazil costly stadiums, poor public transport - Economic Times |publisher=Articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com |date=14 April 2014 |accessdate=7 June 2014 |archive-date=2014-06-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140622015943/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-06-05/news/50359174_1_gil-castello-branco-contas-abertas-sinaenco |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Featured Columnist |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/1663701-the-social-cost-of-brazil-hosting-world-cup-2014 |title=The Social Cost of Brazil Hosting World Cup 2014 |publisher=Bleacher Report |date=6 June 2013 |accessdate=7 June 2014 |archive-date=2014-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org